FBIS3-4469 "drchi061_n_94004" FBIS-CHI-94-061 Document Type:Daily Report 29 Mar 1994 Economic & Agricultural Beijing To Take Stronger Measures Against Fake Commodities OW2903171994 Beijing XINHUA in English 1555 GMT 29 Mar 94 OW2903171994 Beijing XINHUA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Beijing, March 29 (XINHUA) -- A national meeting was held here today to further crack down this year on fake goods and imitations. Xu Penghang, vice minister in charge of the State Economic and Trade Commission, presided over the meeting and urged the administrative bodies to pay major attention to cracking down on phony medicines, foodstuff, export goods, agricultural production materials and building materials and trade marks, and to deal with ten major cases already under investigation. He pointed out that a safeguarding system should be established, adding that more cases of fake goods had been exposed with the joint efforts of procuratorates and local governments. Last year the procuratorates of China dealt with 3,436 cases, recovering a sum of 72.34 million yuan.
